(mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Hubert</b> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a>. He is the author of <i><a href=\"/index.php/Kin_of_the_Stag\" title=\"Kin of the Stag\">Kin of the Stag</a></i>, in which he suggests that <a href=\"/index.php/Galladon_of_Morne\" title=\"Galladon of Morne\">Galladon of Morne</a> was not a warrior of the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a> turned into a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> by singers, but an actual historical figure of more recent times, noting that <a href=\"/index.php/Morne\" title=\"Morne\">Morne</a> was a royal seat of petty kings on the eastern coast of <a href=\"/index.php/Tarth\" title=\"Tarth\">Tarth</a> until the <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_King\" title=\"Storm King\">Storm Kings</a> made them submit, though its ruins were made by <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a> and not the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_stormlands:_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_stormlands:_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Hubert&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_stormlands:_men_of_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span c